Okechukwu Nnodim and ’Femi Asu The Petroleum Products Pricing Regulatory Agency has announced a new price band of N140.80 to N143.80 per litre for Premium Motor Spirit, also known as petrol. The PPPRA, in a circular dated July 1, 2020 to marketers, said, “After a review of the prevailing market fundamentals in the month of June and considering marketers’ realistic operating costs, as much as practicable, we wish to advise a new PMS pump price band of N140.80-N143.80 per litre for the month of July 2020. [READ ALSO]  774,000 jobs: NASS suspends recruitment exercise “All marketers are advised to operate within the indicative prices as advised by the PPPRA.” The agency had on May 31, 2020 announced a price band of N121.50 to N123.50 per litre for the product. Sources at the Abuja headquarters of the agency said the rise in petrol price for July was primarily due to the increase in global crude oil prices, as PMS had been deregulated.